        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued April 3 at 1:26PM CDT by NWS Tulsa OK</headline>
        <description>At 125 PM CDT, Doppler radar indicated a strong thunderstorm over
Burnville, moving northeast at 60 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and penny size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down small tree limbs and blow
around unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation
is possible.

Locations in or near the path include...
Charleston...                     Crossroads...
Central City...                   Dayton...
Milltown...                       Branch...
Vesta...                          Cecil...
Ursula...                         Lavaca...
Altus...                          Denning...
Etna...                           Greenwood...
Alix...                           Bloomer...
Washburn...                       Meg...
Barling...                        Peter Pender...

This includes Interstate 40 in Arkansas between mile markers 31 and
42.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
